active class, making it confusing. Creating a LocatorTest.java makes sense to avoid scaffold-only issues. I plan to use assertj for assertions and ensure that my JUnit methods are package-private. \\n\\nThe first test will check if a null loader falls back correctly, while another will verify that a resource from the Launcher class returns the expected results.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering URI API tests**\\n\\nI'm thinking about testing the URI APIs, but it seems I can focus on the active class instead of dynamic ones. Having just one test might suffice, as long as it provides high coverage. I could test `getClassSource(Locator.class)` to see if it returns correctly in native scenarios, but it appears that resources might not be available. Maybe I could just use a non-existing resource to see how it behaves? That could make for an interesting test!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_QutdFedG54v6ncpTGr2dhrr9|fc_04563a74adf902b50169f6db487aac819e854c76737b048752", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.ant/ant-launcher/1.8.1/src/test/java/org_apache_ant/ant_launcher/LocatorTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_apache_ant.ant_launcher;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException;\nimport java.net.MalformedURLException;\nimport java.net.URL;\n\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.launch.Locator;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class LocatorTest {\n    @Test\n    void getResourceSourceFallsBackFromNullLoaderToLocatorLoader() {\n        String missingResource = \"org/apache/tools/ant/launch/no-such-resource.txt\";\n\n        File nullLoaderSource = Locator.getResourceSource(null, missingResource);\n        File explicitLoaderSource = Locator.getResourceSource(Locator.class.getClassLoader(), missingResource);\n\n        assertThat(nullLoaderSource).isEqualTo(explicitLoaderSource).isNull();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void uriEncodingRoundTripPreservesSpacesAndNonAsciiCharacters() throws UnsupportedEncodingException {\n        String path = \"build directory/ant café.xml\";\n\n        String encoded = Locator.encodeURI(path);\n        String decoded = Locator.decodeUri(encoded);\n\n        assertThat(encoded).contains(\"%20\");\n        assertThat(decoded).isEqualTo(path);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void fileLocationUrlsUseJarFilterWhenDirectoryIsScanned() throws MalformedURLException {\n        File location = new File(\"build/locator-test-libs\");\n        assertThat(location.mkdirs() || location.isDirectory()).isTrue();\n        File jarFile = new File(location, \"ant-launcher-test.jar\");\n        File ignoredFile = new File(location, \"ant-launcher-test.txt\");\n\n        URL[] urls = Locator.getLocationURLs(location, new String[] {\".jar\"});\n\n        assertThat(jarFile).doesNotExist();\n        assertThat(ignoredFile).doesNotExist();\n        assertThat(urls).isEmpty();\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2140, "output": 1836, "cacheRead": 36352, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40328, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777785652933, "responseId": "resp_04563a74adf902b50169f6db35705c819e9df68482932c1d86"}}
